Painted, patinated and waxed bronze.
Fire in the jelly. This one will be bronze.
Off to America. English oak & American black walnut editions of ‘Growing up gets me down’.
The maquette for Alphabetti Spaghetti, from which the full size boxes were scaled.
Our poster for Alphabetti Spaghetti is an edition of 100 screen prints produced with @telegramme. Available from alexchinneck.com and @turnercontemporary.

There is a post box within half a mile of over 98% of the UK population. Wouldn’t it be wonderful if people had the same access to art. This series, titled Alphabetti Spaghetti, will continue to tour and hopefully surprise, greet and delight as many people as possible. Photography by @marcwilmot

Last night I tied three classic British post boxes in knots across the country. The third was tied outside Caxton Works in Canning Town, London, in partnership with @uandiplc and @4ourcreativearts. This post box is permanent. Photography by @marcwilmot. #london

Last night I tied three classic British post boxes in knots across the country. The second was tied on Norborough Road in Tinsley, Sheffield, outside Tinsley Meadows Primary Academy. I look forward to discussing the work with the 400 school children tomorrow. This post box will be in place until Monday before it moves to its next location. Photography by @marcwilmot. #sheffield

Last night I tied three classic British post boxes in knots across the country. The first was tied in Margate, Kent, and will be in place until January 12th as part of #MargateNOW Festival. Photography by @marcwilmot. #margate

Over 200,000 people visited the unzipping building over the last 6 days. My sculptures playfully disrupt our perception of what is physically possible but this project has only been possible because of the brilliant people that built it with me. Ambition gives birth to an idea but collaboration makes it grow. Thank you to everyone who visited the artworks, thank you to everyone who built the artworks with me, thank you to IQOS for this partnership and thanks for having me Milan. #milan #milandesignweek #iqosworld. Photography by @marcwilmot.

‘Richard of York gave battle in Vegas’. You enter the door on the left, climb a staircase to go inside the sculpture and then exit on the right. I wanted to create an interactive and immersive sculptural experience that encouraged people to visit the work in person. 90,000 people visited the unzipping artworks today. #milandesignweek #iqosworld. Photography by @marcwilmot.
Somewhere under the rainbow. #milandesignweek #iqosworld. Photography by @marcwilmot.
Stone. Photography by @marcwilmot. #iqosworld #milandesignweek. Visit Via Tortona 31, Milano.
Goodnight from Milan. Photography by @marcwilmot. #milandesignweek #iqosworld.

We just unveiled our third sculpture at Milan Design Week in partnership with IQOS. An eight metre tall unzipping factory wall at Via Tortona 31. #milandesignweek #iqosworld. Photography by @marcwilmot.

We just unveiled our second sculpture at Milan Design Week. An unzipping concrete floor in partnership with IQOS. We excavated and re-poured the entire factory floor at Via Tortona 31. #milandesignweek #iqosworld. Photography by @marcwilmot.

We just unveiled our new sculpture at Milan Design Week in partnership with IQOS. The seventeen metre wide sculpture unzips a Milanese facade. This is the most ambitious work I’ve ever made - and there are two more to come. See it at Via Tortona 31 all this week. #milandesignweek #iqosworld. Photography by @marcwilmot.
Growing up gets me down. Our latest clock, made from a single piece of American Black Walnut.
Symmetrically smashed mirrors. Two hand carved french polished walnut frames containing 50 pieces of bevelled glass. Photography by @charlesemerson_

I first visited India two years ago and have returned many times since. Last week I paid a visit to the fabricators and foundry that we are collaborating with to produce a major public artwork for the centre of Mumbai. Here is a small component of that sculpture, which opens later this year.
Nervous times

Repaving Memory Lane: Tinsley Rolling Mills. The first print from our new collaboration with Sheffield’s picture archive, in which, history and reality are playfully distorted. Photograph courtesy of picturesheffield.com. #onandupnorth #sheffield
After 100 days, 170 media articles and one wedding (to the wonderful @lu_flux in this photo) our unzipping building comes down next week. See it this weekend for the final time.
